CatDescriptText: The sign in the foreground reads "Fashion Extravaganza and Cabaret Ball given by The JHA Girls, Friday May 7, 1965, 9 P.M. til 1 A.M. at the Workingmen's Civic Club 207 Devilliers St. Purchase Tickets Here $2.50 at door $2.75".
TitMainTitle: Three women wearing leotards with bow ties and sashes with "JHA" inscriptions standing on small stage, including woman at center playing drums, with sign in foreground that reads, "Fashion Extravaganza and Cabaret Ball"
